    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Form of farming that uses steps or terraces on an upland area, to  maximize arable land area by creating horizontal, flat plots for crops. A prime example of the practice was in Pre-Columbian cultures.</Note_Text>
